Sentencas: Layered perovskite oxides have received extensive attention as promising cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) because of their faster diffusion coefficient and oxygen transport kinetics.
Titulo: The effect of calcium doping on the improvement of performance and durability in a layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With the goals of enhancing electrochemical properties and improving the durability, this study focuses on the effect of calcium (Ca) doping in PrBa0.5Sr0.5-xCaxCo2O5+delta (x = 0 and 0.25) layered perovskite oxides through an investigation of their structural characteristics, electrical properties, redox behavior, electrochemical performances, and stability.
Titulo: The effect of calcium doping on the improvement of performance and durability in a layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the temperature range of 100-750 degrees C, the electrical conductivity of PrBa0.5Sr0.25Ca0.25Co2O5+delta (PBSCaCO) is higher than that of Ca-free PrBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+delta (PBSCO).
Titulo: The effect of calcium doping on the improvement of performance and durability in a layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) value of PBSCaCO-GDC (0.079 Omega cm(2)) is lower than that of PBSCO-GDC (0.093 Omega cm(2)) at 600 degrees C, based on a GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: The effect of calcium doping on the improvement of performance and durability in a layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, PBSCaCO-GDC achieves a good performance of 1.83 W cm(-2) at 600 degrees C. PBSCaCO shows a stable power output without observable degradation for 100 h. On the basis of these results, the PBSCaCO cathode is an excellent candidate for IT-SOFC applications.
Titulo: The effect of calcium doping on the improvement of performance and durability in a layered perovskite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
